    "id": "f_csv_9a113d5d11",
    "slug": "how-have-people-come-to-be-taken-in-by-the-phenomenon-of-man-we-must-not-undere",
    "texto": "How have people come to be taken in by The Phenomenon of Man? We must not underestimate the size of the market for works of this kind [pseudoscience/'woo'], for philosophy-fiction. Just as compulsory primary education created a market catered for by cheap dailies and weeklies, so the spread of secondary and latterly tertiary education has created a large population of people, often with well-developed literary and scholarly tastes, who have been educated far beyond their capacity to undertake analytical thought.",
